-- layer-17 §2.1 SOUNDNESS gate: Int arithmetic crossing ±2^30 must NOT truncate.
-- Pre-fix the WasmGC backend unboxed via i31.get_s (31-bit) and computed in i32, so
-- any value/intermediate outside [-2^30, 2^30) wrapped.  Now Ints box into $boxint
-- and arithmetic runs in i64; this fixture's >2^30 results match the native oracle.
--
-- crossUp  = 2^30-1 + 1            = 1073741824   (crosses the i31 ceiling)
-- prod     = 10^6 * 10^6           = 10^12        (a 40-bit intermediate)
-- big      = 2147483647 + 2147483647 = 4294967294 (> i32 signed max)
-- eqBig    = (prod == 1000000000000)  must be True (boxed-Int equality)
-- The final value combines them so a single wrong sub-result changes the output.
crossUp = 1073741823 + 1

prod = 1000000 * 1000000

big = 2147483647 + 2147483647

eqBig = prod == 1000000000000

-- if the equality and the crossing both hold, fold everything into one large Int.
main = if eqBig then crossUp + prod + big else 0 - 1
